commit.message:
Fix open-uri usage to use URI.open

Previously, open-uri redefined open to handle URIs as well as file
paths. This is no longer the case, presumably for security concerns.

Specify a safer version of Rake

Fixes CVE-2020-8130

Move tests to RSpec

Test::Unit is no longer shipped with Ruby, and I now prefer RSpec, so
this is a good opportunity to switch. There is more to do here - the
assert_encode and assert_decode methods aren't idiomatic - but it works.

Use chr instead of pack

It expresses the intention more clearly, and it's about twice as fast.

Use codepoints instead of unpack

It's clearer in terms of intention, and marginally faster.
Release 4.3.4

Don't rebuild mappings unnecessarily

If you need to rebuild them, just delete them. This is unusual, so we
shouldn't force people to rebuild them if they haven't made a change.

Remove erroneous Iodot mapping

This does not exist in
ftp://ftp.unicode.org/Public/MAPPINGS/VENDORS/MISC/SGML.TXT

See https://github.com/threedaymonk/htmlentities/issues/19

Fix broken entity generator

* Works with 1.9+
* Paths corrected
* Run by the default Rake task where needed

The generated files are unchanged.

Release 4.3.3

Fixes duplicate key warning in Ruby 2.2.0.
Update history for 4.3.2 (I forgot)

Remove duplicated key: 'inodot'

This key is already defined at the above.
Version bump for packaging changes
Add licence (and description) to gemspec
Ignore temporary files
We can use require_relative in 1.9+
Update copyright year and refer to separate file
Simplify relative path
Move all encoding steps to methods
Tweak coding style
Explain what post_process is

Rename common.rb -> test_helper.rb

This is more, well, common.
Remove support for Ruby 1.8
Use Bundler for development
Including setup.rb is probably an archaism now
Add link to canonical source
Add code highlighting in README
Release 4.3.1.
Only run the interoperability tests if an environment variable is set.
